params._optimal: is the input number representing the optimal*

params._InterestRateModel: is the address of this MoneyMarketInstances InterestRateModel*

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

borrow(uint256).notice: borrow is used to take out a loan from in MoneyMarketInstance's underlying asset

calculateAHRexchangeRate(uint256,uint256.notice: calculateAHRInterest is used to calculate the earned interest for the High Risk pool

calculateALRexchangeRate(uint256,uint256.notice: calculateALRInterest is used to calculate the earned interest for the Low Risk pool

calculateFee(uint256).notice: calculateFee is used to calculate the fee earned

calculateLoanInterest(uint256,uint256).notice: calculateLoanInterest is used to calculate the interest for a loan

methods.constructor: the constructor function is fired during the contract deployment process. The constructor can only be fired once and is used to initialize the MoneyMakerInstance and deploy its associated AHR && ALR token contracts

lendToAHRpool(uint256).notice: lendToAHRpool is used to lend assets to a MoneyMarketInstance's High Risk pool

lendToALRpool(uint256).notice: lendToAHRpool is used to lend assets to a MoneyMarketInstance's Low Risk pool

redeemAHR(uint256).notice: redeemAHR is used to redeem AHR toke for its underlying asset + interest

redeemALR(uint256).notice: redeemALR is used to redeem ALR toke for its underlying asset + interest

repay().notice: repay is used to repay a loan

setBaseRate(uint256).notice: setBaseRate allows the owner of this contract to set the baseRate

setCollateralizationRatio(uint256).notice: setCollateralizationRatio allows the owner of this contract to set the collateralizationRatio

setFee(uint256).notice: setFee allows the owner of this contract to set the fee

setMultiplierM(uint256).notice: setMultiplierM allows the owner of this contract to set the multiplierM

setMultiplierN(uint256).notice: setMultiplierM allows the owner of this contract to set the multiplierN

setOptimal(uint256).notice: setOptimal allows the owner of this contract to set the optimal
